    "narrative": "The offensive engine for Ghost Ride the WHIP relies heavily on the McCullers Jr. matchup today, making **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.36) our most potent asset. His aggressive baserunning profile against a slow delivery elevates his floor, and alongside **Giancarlo Stanton** (64.64) and **Jose Caballero** (56.31), he stands to benefit from the favorable matchup against an exploitable arm. While **Trevor Story** (75.93) carries a lower base projection than **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, he is our strongest play relative to park factors; playing in a hitter-friendly environment against Young provides a +16% boost, making him a cornerstone of today's 5x5 pursuit. Conversely, **Brice Turang** (49.29) remains in the lineup purely for his leadoff spot, as he faces the stiffest test of the day against Skenes, whose elite efficiency mandates a high-risk outlook for our MI slot.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Seiya Suzuki** (45.02), who narrowly missed the cut. While his projected efficiency sits comfortably above the 40-point floor, the combination of a pending lineup status and the negative SP Skill adjustment from Sheehan\u2019s arm pushed him behind the optimized efficiency of **Alex Freeland** (47.84) and **Tyler Soderstrom** (47.90). Though **Tyler Soderstrom** faces a challenge in Eovaldi, his platoon advantage provided just enough upside to maintain his utility spot. We remain wary of the \"Elite Catcher\" penalty applied to **Brice Turang**, and we are monitoring the weather closely; if any of the high-score starters are scratched due to late lineup shifts, **Seiya Suzuki** is the priority pivot to protect our daily game caps.",
